	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002065_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<!--Hand 01 40 top left--><!--hand 02 68010 superscript D top right-->
<lb/><p rend="right">Hamilton 13<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi><choice><abbr>Sept<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi></abbr><expan>September</expan></choice></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1864</p>
<lb/><p>My dear Sunley</p>
<lb/><p>I got your letter 
<lb/>last night and am like 
<lb/>yourself sorry that 
<lb/>we had no opportunity 
<lb/>of conversing together 
<lb/>about the future, but 
<lb/>I was not sure that I 
<lb/>should not meet you 
<lb/>at home in England. 
<lb/>You ought to have 
<lb/>mentioned what things 
<lb/>you required and I 
<lb/>should have written 
<lb/>to M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi><unclear cert="high">Soares</unclear> to send them 
<lb/>and if I needed them 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002065_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/>again they could be returned</p>
<lb/><p>I am glad the cart suits 
<lb/>you. I am going out 
<lb/>again in a few months 
<lb/>but to the <unclear cert="high">North</unclear> of 
<lb/>Zanzibar. I am sorry 
<lb/>that you did not advise 
<lb/>Captain <unclear cert="medium">Fraezer</unclear> to try his 
<lb/>sugar plantation on the 
<lb/>mainland. as he will 
<lb/>have all the difficulties 
<lb/>to contend against in the 
<lb/>slave owners over again 
<lb/>which have always hampered 
<lb/>you. Have you still 
<lb/>the intention of trying 
<lb/>what you can do in a 
<lb/>wider sphere on the 
<lb/>continent? I have kept 
<lb/>my steamer to see if I 
<lb/>can get a good <unclear cert="medium">spurt</unclear>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002065_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/>up some of the rivers &amp; 
<lb/>will write if I do not 
<lb/>visit you.</p>
<lb/><p>I am going to the 
<lb/>meeting of the British 
<lb/>Association at Bath 
<lb/>and am bothered what 
<lb/>to say as public speaking 
<lb/>is totally against the 
<lb/>grain in my 
<w>com-<lb break="no"/>position.</w><!--two hyphens--> I wish you 
<lb/>or <unclear cert="high">Seedy</unclear> would do it 
<lb/>for me. <unclear cert="high">Rae's</unclear> friends 
<lb/>have been enquiring 
<lb/>for him. I write this 
<lb/>scrawl simply to let 
<lb/>you know that I have 
<lb/>heard from you and 
<lb/>will write again when 
<lb/>I have time</p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002065_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
<!-- Confirm: pb was mistakenly coded as lb -->
<lb/><p>and am ever yours</p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><!--Hand 03 --><choice><abbr>Sepr</abbr><expan>September</expan></choice> 13<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">h</hi></hi> 1864</p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><choice><abbr>Rec<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">d</hi></hi></abbr><expan>Received</expan></choice><choice><abbr>Feb</abbr><expan>February</expan></choice> 11/65</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">Ans 
<lb/><!--end of different hand--></p>
<lb/><p>I think the consular 
<lb/>uniform is on its 
<lb/>way home. &amp; I may 
<lb/>need it. I hear you 
<lb/>are retired. Is that true? 
<lb/>It was by way 
<lb/>of India I came home</p>
<lb/><p><choice><abbr>Comp<hi rend="sup">ts</hi></abbr><expan>Compliments</expan></choice> to Rae.</p>
			
